  <data name="swagger_remarks_codigobarra_createupdateordelete" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided, it notifies the automation of the creation, overwriting or deletion of barcodes through integration with the Automation Interpreter.
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
  <data name="swagger_remarks_confirmacionentrada_send" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided by the Automation Interpreter, it transfers the confirmed stock to picking locations and the unconfirmed remainder to reject locations due to integration with the WMS.
        
             When consuming this API, the Automation Interpreter includes an "X-Hub-Signature" HTTP header that contains the JSON hash of the incoming parameter.
             calculated from the "HMACSHA512" algorithm and a secret shared with the client application that makes this API available.
             The specific implementation of this API may use the aforementioned header to verify the authenticity of the received message.
             To do this, it recalculates the hash of the incoming JSON, applying the same algorithm and shared secret with the Automation Interpreter.
             and checks that it matches the one received through the HTTP header.
        
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
  <data name="swagger_remarks_confirmacionsalida_send" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided by the Automation Interpreter, it prepares the confirmed stock and cancels the remaining unconfirmed by integrating with the WMS.
             
             When consuming this API, the Automation Interpreter includes an "X-Hub-Signature" HTTP header that contains the JSON hash of the incoming parameter.
             calculated from the "HMACSHA512" algorithm and a secret shared with the client application that makes this API available.
             The specific implementation of this API may use the aforementioned header to verify the authenticity of the received message.
             To do this, it recalculates the hash of the incoming JSON, applying the same algorithm and shared secret with the Automation Interpreter.
             and checks that it matches the one received through the HTTP header.
         
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
  <data name="swagger_remarks_entrada_entradastock" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided, it notifies the entry of stock to the automation by integration with the Automation Interpreter.
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
  <data name="swagger_remarks_notificacionajustestock_send" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided by the Automation Interpreter, it generates stock adjustments through integration with the WMS.
             
             When consuming this API, the Automation Interpreter includes an "X-Hub-Signature" HTTP header that contains the JSON hash of the incoming parameter.
             calculated from the "HMACSHA512" algorithm and a secret shared with the client application that makes this API available.
             The specific implementation of this API may use the aforementioned header to verify the authenticity of the received message.
             To do this, it recalculates the hash of the incoming JSON, applying the same algorithm and shared secret with the Automation Interpreter.
             and checks that it matches the one received through the HTTP header.
             
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
  <data name="swagger_remarks_producto_update" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided, it notifies the automation of product updates through integration with the Automation Interpreter.
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
